  1→# EXAMPLE.md — How to Add Sections to This App
  2→
  3→This file shows concrete, copy-paste examples for extending the app with new sections and state.
  4→
  5→---
  6→
  7→## Example 1: Minimal Static Section
  8→
  9→The simplest possible section — no props, no state, just content.
 10→
 11→**`src/components/sections/HelloSection.tsx`**
 12→```tsx
 13→export default function HelloSection() {
 14→  return (
 15→    <section className="section-card hello-section">
 16→      <h3>Hello World</h3>
 17→      <p>This is a new section.</p>
 18→    </section>
 19→  );
 20→}
 21→```
 22→
 23→**Register it in `src/App.tsx`** — add the import at the top with the other section imports:
 24→```tsx
 25→import HelloSection from './components/sections/HelloSection';
 26→```
 27→
 28→Then add it into the render tree. Find the `tab-content--showcase-flow` div and add your wrapper:
